CRAWFISH BEIGNETS! they're a must. my friend told me about this place and i decided to try it today. she recommended the crawfish beignets and the sweet potato pancakes. i'm not a fan of sweets during breakfast so i opted for the grillades and grits instead. it was good but super filling, i only ate a third of it. the grits were creamy but i got tired of them after a bit. my friend got the jambalaya and boy, that was good. maybe i'll get that next time... or try one of their delicious looking po boys. definitely get the crawfish beignets!! they're filled with crawfish and cheesy goodness.

Honestly, the only thing you need to know is this: they do delivery fried chicken, AND it gets delivered crispy! Blew my mind, but it's also delicious.

You better have an appetite when you go because the food is so damn good you're gonna want to eat everything on your plate. The Watermelon Sweet Tea is Yummy.

My friend Cali was very impressed and she is very picky about southern soul food. Parking was not too bad before noon.

Shrimp and grits were delicious. My favorite part of tasting the bacon and the cheesy grits. Brought out so much flavor. Tried the crawfish beignets and the hush puppies as well. Really really really loved the crawfish beignets

Ok so talk about metered parking, it is like $3 an hour there.....so try to find a broken meter or residential parking. Ridiculous in my opinion. Came back on a Friday at 12:30pm cause most people are working right? Wrong there were like 13 people ahead of us but we only had to wait 30 mins. They did an excellent job in turning over tables. Finally got that beignet flight. Definitely worth it. With the plain, I ate it with their peach jam, delicious. The chocolate was really rich. The apple one was like eating a fresh apple pie. I would definitely recommend having the flight at least once to try all of them. Also tried their special the creole shrimp pot pie. Really good too. I loved the salad that came with it too. The dressing was light but flavorful. Oh and that refillable watermelon ice tea. Yummmm. The watermelon was sweeter this time around most likely cause it's summer and watermelons are in season. Service was good. Very fast paced but they're very attentive. They never left a glass empty. Don't expect to chit chat with your servers though cause they're scrambling around. That's how the line goes by real quick. Another awesome experience at Brenda's.

''Oh, there's a line of people. That must be it!'' 10am on a Saturday morning and one of my best friends (Tram http://www.yelp.com/user_details?userid=0QeJC2inz6P-OVzROU_LNw) and I were trying to locate Brenda's for a Brunch to kick start our day in The City, knowing that some people do wait as long long as 2 or 3 hours to be seated I was not at all surprised that a group had already formed outside. To be seated you write your name and number of people in your party on the chalk board and wait to be called. I think we got fairly lucky and didn't have to wait too long. Maybe 55 minutes. As soon as we were seated we were approached by our server offering drinks and then set about trying desperately to decide what we wanted. It was a hard task and I got so overwhelmed that I went for one of the simplest items on the menu - French toast and a cup of Gumbo while Tram went for a special - Pulled Pork Egg's Benedict. I won't lie, as soon as I saw her plate I had a severe case of ''meal envy''. Damn my indecisiveness and being scared to try something new! (don't laugh.. I've never had Egg's Benedict before. It's not something that is all that popular among us Brits). As it was the Beignet's that first had me add Brenda's to my Yelp bookmarks we decided to get a portion of them to share, we went for the Chocolate as it was something we both like (http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/brendas-french-soul-food-san-francisco?select=AVNATO7LC5hdzdheXjXFMw#WbDkKcsl-c0mfFazEa4Awg) - $6. They were a lot bigger than they look in the pictures and seeing the expression on Tram's face as she bit into one first I knew I was going to be in for a treat so I immediately tucked in too. Freshly cooked and piping hot they are crispy on the outside and fluffy inside with mountains of molten Chocolate. Not some nasty cheap Chocolate either (Hershey's or Nestle) but Ghirardelli, Yum! They do have a lot of powdered sugar on which I had to scrape a lot off but otherwise they're pretty close to perfect. Doesn't it look good?: http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/brendas-french-soul-food-san-francisco?select=AVNATO7LC5hdzdheXjXFMw#msTW5FqSgRCbGjDAtUKuYg Despite the previously mentioned meal envy I did still really enjoy my French Toast too (http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/brendas-french-soul-food-san-francisco?select=AVNATO7LC5hdzdheXjXFMw#ypiHEiXbxgp8DKhMr98Zkw) - $7.75. I was expecting 2 slices but instead got 3 really thick slices and cooked nicely, not too Eggy with a side of Syrup. However after having had the Beignet I could only eat 1 slice and had the get the rest to go which still tasted good the following day. (http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/brendas-french-soul-food-san-francisco?select=AVNATO7LC5hdzdheXjXFMw#q7RtcodGno-d7VgTWwr3FA) The Gumbo (http://www.yelp.com/biz_photos/brendas-french-soul-food-san-francisco?select=AVNATO7LC5hdzdheXjXFMw#bAyA9P_SPvxMvJEUd-N_Xw) - $3.50 is something I had not had before (it's essentially just a southern style soup) so I have nothing to compare to but I also found it enjoyable. It was packed full of Okra with a few small chunks of Chicken yet I couldn't find the Sausage which was a little disappointing. Still.. hearty and flavorful, I would be likely to order it again. I had a very enjoyable experience at Brenda's and not just because of the delicious food but also the company I was in. When I moved to California almost 4 years ago I never thought I would meet such an amazing person and great friend. Not only did Tram drive all the way from Santa Cruz (and me from Tracy) for us to spend the day together but also as soon as the check came she whipped it away and wouldn't let me pay as it was a ''Birthday'' treat for me. I wasn't even allowed to leave the tip.. bless her *heart*. My advise if you're reading these reviews contemplating coming here? DO IT! The wait may be scary but it's so worth it. I fully intend on returning myself, that Pulled Pork Benedict WILL be mine one day. Then I feel I can judge a rate them a little better. *TIP* They can do individual Beignet's for you if you ask. We only discovered this from seeing a neighboring table do so. ** Featured on TV show ''Roadtrip with G. Garvin.'' **

Incredible place for brunch and especially on this rainy day! Definitely the place for some food that will warm you up so you can go back to bed and snuggle. We came early and didn't have to wait more than 5 minutes.     ''Oh, there's a line of people. That must be it!''

    10am on a Saturday morning and one of my best friends (Tram yelp.com/user_details?us…) and I were trying to locate Brenda's for a Brunch to kick start our day in The City, knowing that some people do wait as long long as 2 or 3 hours to be seated  I was not at all surprised that a group had already formed outside. To be seated you write your name and number of people in your party on the chalk board and wait to be called. I think we got fairly lucky and didn't have to wait too long. Maybe 55 minutes.

    As soon as we were seated we were approached by our server offering drinks and then set about trying desperately to decide what we wanted. It was a hard task and I got so overwhelmed that I went for one of the simplest items on the menu - French toast and a cup of Gumbo while Tram went for a special - Pulled Pork Egg's Benedict. I won't lie, as soon as I saw her plate I had a severe case of ''meal envy''. Damn my indecisiveness and being scared to try something new! (don't laugh.. I've never had Egg's Benedict before.  It's not something that is all that popular among us Brits).

    As it was the Beignet's that first had me add Brenda's to my Yelp bookmarks we decided to get a portion of them to share, we went for the Chocolate as it was something we both like (yelp.com/biz_photos/bren…) - $6. They were a lot bigger than they look in the pictures and seeing the expression on Tram's face as she bit into one first  I knew I was going to be in for a treat so I immediately tucked in too.
    Freshly cooked and piping hot they are crispy on the outside and fluffy inside with mountains of molten Chocolate. Not some nasty cheap Chocolate either (Hershey's or Nestle) but Ghirardelli, Yum! They do have a lot of powdered sugar on which I had to scrape a lot off but otherwise they're pretty close to perfect.
    Doesn't it look good?: yelp.com/biz_photos/bren…

    Despite the previously mentioned meal envy I did still really enjoy my French Toast too (yelp.com/biz_photos/bren…) - $7.75. I was expecting 2 slices but instead got 3 really thick slices and cooked nicely, not too Eggy with a side of Syrup. However after having had the Beignet I could only eat 1 slice and had the get the rest to go which still tasted good the following day. (yelp.com/biz_photos/bren…)

    The Gumbo (yelp.com/biz_photos/bren…) - $3.50 is something I had not had before (it's essentially just a southern style soup) so I have nothing to compare to but I also found it enjoyable. It was packed full of Okra with a few small chunks of Chicken yet I couldn't find the Sausage which was a little disappointing. Still.. hearty and flavorful, I would be likely to order it again.

    I had a very enjoyable experience at Brenda's and not just because of the delicious food but also the company I was in. When I moved to California almost 4 years ago I never thought I would meet such an amazing person and great friend. Not only did Tram drive all the way from Santa Cruz (and me from Tracy) for us to spend the day together but also as soon as the check came she whipped it away and wouldn't let me pay as it was a ''Birthday'' treat for me. I wasn't even allowed to leave the tip.. bless her *heart*.

    My advise if you're reading these reviews contemplating coming here? DO IT! The wait may be scary but it's so worth it. I fully intend on returning myself, that Pulled Pork Benedict WILL be mine one day. Then I feel I can judge a rate them a little better.

    *TIP*
    They can do individual Beignet's for you if you ask. We only discovered this from seeing a neighboring table do so.

    ** Featured on TV show ''Roadtrip with G. Garvin.'' **

    2 photos

    Incredible place for brunch and especially on this rainy day! Definitely the place for some food that will warm you up so you can go back to bed and snuggle.

    We came early and didn't have to wait more than 5 minutes. Got the flight of beignets -plain, chocolate, catfish, and Granny Smith apple (which we were too full to eat there, but were great as an afternoon snack.

    The grits were incredible, better than the hash. The biscuit was fluffy and great with the jam on the table.

    We got the fried chicken eggs Benedict (my fav) and my dining companion loved the hang time fry (with fried oysters, so yea.)

    Also, don't forget the watermelon sweet tea, which was da bomb.
